## Stack
- Frontend: React 18 + TypeScript (strict) + Vite (port 1420) + Monaco + Zustand
- Shell: Tauri 2 (Rust, MSVC on Windows)
- 5 platforms: Windows, macOS, Linux, iOS, Android
- LLM: BYO key (OpenAI / Anthropic / OpenRouter), no backend
- Voice: Web Speech API (daily driver) + cpal + whisper-rs (on-device desktop, m2c-native feature)

## Build commands
- npm run typecheck     # npx tsc -b, must be 0 errors
- npm run lint          # npm run typecheck, must be 0 errors
- npm test              # npx vitest run, 1293/1293 expected
- npm run build         # vite production build
- cd src-tauri && cargo check               # 0 errors, 0 warnings
- cd src-tauri && cargo test --lib          # 413/413 expected
- cd src-tauri && cargo test --tests        # 24/24 expected
- cd src-tauri && cargo check --features mobile
- cd src-tauri && cargo check --features m2c-native --lib   # needs libclang + cmake

## The 7 rules (PR-checked)
1. Spacing: use tokens.css scale (--space-1 = 4px through --space-12), never hardcode px.
2. No new tokens without a phase plan. Design system: src/shared/styles/tokens.css.
3. No new components without owner confirmation. Reuse src/shared/components/. Grep target.
4. No new dependencies without owner confirmation (npm + cargo).
5. Tests for every new feature. Vitest (JS) + #[cfg(test)] mod tests (Rust).
6. State in Zustand (src/screens/<X>/state/<X>Store.ts or src/shared/state/), not Context, not useState for cross-component.
7. Update HANDOFF.md + CHANGELOG.md for every phase. Decisions are numbered; new ones go in the next slot after the last used (currently #189).

## Architecture thumb-rules
- Tauri commands are thin one-liners in src-tauri/src/lib.rs; logic in src-tauri/src/<feature>.rs.
- JS IPC wrappers live in src/ipc/<feature>.ts (typed wrappers around `invoke`).
- Do not add new routes to appStore.ts/main.tsx without owner confirmation.
- The voice hook (src/shared/hooks/useVoiceCapture.ts) is the unified entry point for all STT providers.

## Cargo features
- default: desktop build, no m2c-native, no mobile
- m2c-native: pulls whisper-rs; needs libclang + cmake + C++ toolchain
- metal / cuda / vulkan: m2c-native + hardware acceleration
- mobile: pulls tauri-plugin-stronghold + iota_stronghold; for Android secrets
- internal-tools: hidden dev-only commands

## Voice architecture
- Daily driver: Web Speech API (src/voice/webSpeechSTT.ts) — works on Windows / macOS / iOS, no build cost.
- On-device desktop: cpal mic capture (src-tauri/src/stt_capture.rs) + 16 kHz resample + whisper-rs (src-tauri/src/stt_inference.rs, m2c-native gated).
- On-device mobile (future): Swift SFSpeechRecognizer on iOS, Kotlin SpeechRecognizer on Android. Contracts in docs/plugins/lipi-stt-{ios,android}/README.md.
- JS-side: src/shared/hooks/useVoiceCapture.ts unifies all three.
- UI: src/screens/SettingsProvider/components/{OnDeviceCard, WebSpeechCard, NativeDictationCard}.tsx.

## "Do not" list
- Do not touch C:\Users\Pv Vimal Nair\lifeof\.
- Do not add npm / cargo deps without owner confirmation.
- Do not change whisper-rs version (pinned to 0.16, Decision #164).
- Do not change tauri.conf.json mobile block (pinned, Decision #185).
- Do not skip the HANDOFF.md / CHANGELOG.md update for phase work.
