- Do not run cargo install of new toolchains without owner confirmation.

## When working on UI
- Read docs/ENGINEERING.md first.
- Check src/shared/components/ for an existing component before creating a new one.
- Use design tokens (src/shared/styles/tokens.css) for all colors, spacing, typography.
- Match Figma exactly: spacing, font sizes, colors, border radius. No eyeballing.
- Every button needs onTap/onPressed. Every image needs error fallback. Every form needs validation.
- Touch targets minimum 44x44 pixels.
- Always handle safe areas (notch, home indicator) properly.

## When working on Rust
- IPC commands go in src-tauri/src/lib.rs as one-liners; logic in a module under src-tauri/src/.
- pub use the public function from lib.rs so tests can call it without going through the Tauri command layer.
- Tests use #[cfg(test)] mod tests inside the same file, with the lipi_lib:: prefix on the function name in integration tests.
- For cpal::Stream (or any type that is !Send), use a dedicated std::thread + spawn_blocking to join — see src-tauri/src/stt_capture.rs for the pattern.
- Conditional compilation: #[cfg(feature = "m2c-native")] for real Whisper, #[cfg(not(mobile))] for cpal, #[cfg(feature = "mobile")] for Stronghold.

## When working on JS / React
- State in Zustand stores (no Context-as-state, no useState for cross-component).
- IPC wrappers in src/ipc/<feature>.ts are typed around `invoke<T>(...)`.
- New screens: one folder under src/screens/, with components/, hooks/, state/ subfolders.
- Use the useVoiceCapture hook for any voice capture. Don't go to the Tauri APIs directly.
- Match the 7 ENGINEERING.md rules for spacing, colors, typography, components.

## Pickup points (in priority order)
1. iOS Swift SFSpeechRecognizer plugin (Mac + Xcode 16+).
   Contract: docs/plugins/lipi-stt-ios/README.md.
2. Android Kotlin SpeechRecognizer plugin (Mac or Linux + Android Studio).
   Contract: docs/plugins/lipi-stt-android/README.md.
3. Real .ipa / .aab builds (cargo tauri {ios,android} build).
4. App Store + Play Store uploads (metadata in docs/store-metadata/).
5. Windows code signing (TAURI_SIGNING_PRIVATE_KEY, WINDOWS_CERT_FILE).
6. Auto-updater end-to-end (needs a GitHub release).
